api/exerciseFn.html.title: exerciseFn
api/exerciseFn.html.body:
exerciseFn
Usage: excerciseFn(sym)
Exercises the fn named by sym (a symbol) by applying it to
n (default 10) generated samples of its args spec. When fspec is
supplied its arg spec is used, and symOrF can be a fn.  Returns a
sequence of tuples of [args, ret].
Source
Example:
const s = require('speculaas');
const {isBoolean, isString} = s.utils;

api/multiSpec.html.title: multiSpec
api/multiSpec.html.body:
multiSpec
Usage: multiSpec(mm retag)
Takes the name of a spec/predicate-returning multimethod and a
tag-restoring keyword or fn (retag).  Returns a spec that when
conforming or explaining data will pass it to the multimethod to get
an appropriate spec. You can e.g. use multiSpec to dynamically and
extensibly associate specs with 'tagged' data (i.e. data where one
of the fields indicates the shape of the rest of the structure).
Source
Note: NodeJS doesn't have multimethods, so you will have to use a library like
genfun here.
Example:
const s = require('speculaas');

api/unform.html.title: unform
api/unform.html.body:
unform
Usage: unform(spec, x)
Given a spec and a value created by or compliant with a call to
'conform' with the same spec, returns a value with all conform
destructuring undone.
Source
Example:
const s = require('speculaas');
const isEven = s.utils;

s.def('::small', s.or(':even', isEven, ':small', x => x
